%3Cp%3EAndy%20Jassy%20is%20set%20on%20reshaping%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-amazon-history-facts-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmazon%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20startup-like%20structure%2C%20despite%20the%20tech%20giant%20employing%20over%20one%20million%20people%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20flatten%20our%20organizations%2C%20to%20move%20faster%20and%20to%20drive%20more%20ownership%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Amazon%20CEO%20said%20Tuesday%20during%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20Review%20Leadership%20Summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20that%20when%20companies%20scale%2C%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Ball%20sorts%20of%20ways%26quot%3B%20they%20can%20start%20to%20slow%20down.%20In%20an%20effort%20to%20emulate%20the%20workflow%20of%20a%20startup%2C%20Amazon%20plans%20to%20increase%20the%20ratio%20of%20individual%20contributors%20to%20managers%20by%2015%25%2C%20and%20has%20also%20mandated%20a%205-day%20return%20to%20office%20to%20help%20drive%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20isn't%20necessarily%20looking%20to%20revert%20to%20its%20venture-backed%20days%2C%20but%20it's%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20regain%20some%20of%20the%20agility%20it%20had%20early%20on.%20Jassy%20said%20these%20are%20the%20six%20things%20big%20companies%20should%20do%20to%20feel%20like%20a%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286340db5-2965-45d7-80a7-9c4bd257a152%5C%22%3E1.%20Seek%20solutions%20to%20real%20customer%20problems%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20that%20while%20a%20lot%20of%20tech%20companies%20%26quot%3Bfall%20in%20love%20with%20technology%26quot%3B%20and%20build%20interesting%20products%2C%20they%20fail%20to%20solve%20%26quot%3Banything%20remarkable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20startups%20are%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20solve%20customer%20problems%2C%20the%20Amazon's%20CEO%20said.%20With%20limited%20time%20and%20funding%20available%2C%20founders%20need%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvc-founders-share-5-things-to-consider-when-starting-company-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaser-focused%20on%20building%20a%20product%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20will%20make%20a%20lasting%20impact%20on%20their%20target%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20we%20got%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20spend%20our%20time%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20added%20that%20even%20in%20times%20of%20tariff%20uncertainty%20and%20geopolitical%20risk%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandy-jassy-tells-ceos-to-stay-focused-amid-tariff-risk-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20has%20continued%20to%20tell%20itself%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Bhere%20to%20make%20customers'%20lives%20easier%20and%20better.%26quot%3B%20The%20CEO%20said%20all%20of%20Amazon's%20businesses%20have%20areas%20that%20can%20be%20improved%20for%20customers%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20it's%20trying%20to%20stay%20focused%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a13a7641-556d-460b-a94c-cdbf36c47859%5C%22%3E2.%20Hire%20a%20lot%20of%20builders%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuccessful-businesses-secret-funding-job-company-growth-money-financing-startups-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrong%20culture%20of%20innovation%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20often%20a%20distinguishing%20factor%20of%20a%20startup.%20Jassy%20said%20that%20companies%20need%20to%20have%20a%20disproportionate%20number%20of%20builders%2C%20which%20he%20defines%20as%20people%20who%20like%20to%20invent%20products.%20Those%20people%20%26quot%3Bdissect%20the%20customer%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20figure%20out%20where%20there%20are%20gaps%2C%20and%20then%20recreate%20the%20product%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20the%20process%20of%20building%20often%20begins%20with%20listening%20to%20what%20customers%20are%20struggling%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20listening%20to%20them%20and%20you%20understand%20the%20need%2C%20then%20you%20can%20invent%20on%20their%20behalf%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demand%20for%20innovation%20is%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-return-to-office-flexible-work-europe-us-rto-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20enacted%20a%20five-day%20return-to-office%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Jassy%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Binvention%20is%20stronger%26quot%3B%20when%20employees%20can%20work%20together%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2235df505f-be46-4c1d-bee9-f761cd74feaf%5C%22%3E3.%20Think%20like%20an%20owner%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20companies%20that%20want%20to%20operate%20like%20startups%20also%20need%20owners.%20That%20means%20people%20%26quot%3Bwho%20really%20feel%20accountable%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CEO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20people%20to%20think%20about%2C%20what%20would%20I%20do%20if%20this%20were%20my%20money%3F%20What%20would%20I%20do%20if%20I%20owned%20all%20the%20resources%3F%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20the%20company's%20effort%20to%20flatten%20its%20workforce%20is%20about%20making%20employees%20return%20to%20that%20ownership%20mindset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d105afc-5e4b-4983-87ae-b02eb2e6d9e0%5C%22%3E4.%20Move%20quick%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20been%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20slash%20its%20bureaucratic%20practices%2C%20whether%20through%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandy-jassy-advice-cut-bureaucracy-management-layers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bno%20bureaucracy%26quot%3B%20email%20alias%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20by%20reducing%20management%20layers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20you%20get%20bigger%2C%20especially%20as%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20managers%2C%20they%20keep%20layering%20in%20processes%2C%20and%20pretty%20soon%20you%20have%20process%20upon%20process%20upon%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20really%20slows%20people%20down%20so%20they%20can't%20get%20the%20real%20work%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20former%20role%20when%20he%20was%20managing%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%2C%20Jassy%20said%20he%20spoke%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20CEOs%20who%20would%20tell%20him%20they%20were%20too%20large%20to%20move%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20he%20believes%20speed%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bleadership%20decision.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20if%20companies%20want%20to%20move%20fast%2C%20Jassy%20said%20they%20need%20to%20figure%20out%20what's%20slowing%20them%20down%20and%20get%20rid%20of%20those%20barriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2290c05dac-c7a5-4a83-a24d-eb13542ce440%5C%22%3E5.%20'Be%20scrappy'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20that%20companies%20can't%20assign%2050%20to%20100%20people%20for%20every%20new%20project%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20completed.%20When%20Amazon%20started%20its%20computing%20service%2C%20it%20had%2013%20people%2C%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20get%20going%20with%20a%20small%20number%20of%20people%20and%20build%20something%20that%20people%20actually%20find%20resonant%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20companies%20can%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20iterating%20from%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22100f6d37-3940-4f03-aea0-723e6463b92a%5C%22%3E6.%20Take%20risks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20companies%20expand%2C%20they%20often%20become%20increasingly%20risk-averse%2C%20Jassy%20said.%20The%20CEO%20said%20that%20highly%20driven%2C%20Type%20A%20personalities%20can%20fall%20into%20the%20mindset%20of%20playing%20it%20safe.%20Those%20types%20of%20people%2C%20whom%20Amazon%20often%20hires%2C%20aren't%20used%20to%20failure%20and%20worry%20about%20being%20%26quot%3Bostracized%20if%20they%20get%20it%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bonly%2