s%20for%20Critics%20Choice%20Association%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAlex%20Costa%20quit%20his%20dream%20job%20at%20YouTube%20for%20another%20dream%3A%20becoming%20a%20full-time%20content%20creator.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20a%20men's%20lifestyle%20vlogger%2C%20brand%20deals%20made%20him%20a%20millionaire.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20Costa's%20own%20grooming%20brand%20Forte%20Series%20is%20on%20track%20to%20do%20%2410%20million%20in%20revenue%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20the%20former%20YouTube%20employee%20Alex%20Costa%2C%20who%20left%20the%20company%20to%20become%20a%20full-time%20content%20creator%20and%20men's%20hair%20care%20entrepreneur.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20first%20hired%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fyoutube%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20work%20in%20the%20gaming%20division%20after%20six%20rounds%20of%20interviews%2C%20it%20was%20the%20happiest%20moment%20of%20my%20life.%20But%20I%20joined%20with%20another%20dream%20in%20mind%3A%20being%20a%20full-time%20content%20creator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20been%20entrepreneurial.%20I'd%20started%20a%20channel%20before%20I%20got%20hired%2C%20and%20held%20various%20jobs%20in%20the%20online%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fgaming%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egaming%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20joined%20YouTube%2C%20I%20already%20had%20about%20130%2C000%20subscribers%2C%20which%20still%20didn't%20feel%20like%20enough%20to%20branch%20out%20on%20my%20own.%20But%20the%20company%20was%20supportive%20as%20I%20continued%20building%20the%20channel%20while%20I%20worked%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202017%2C%20there%20was%20a%20transition%20in%20my%20content.%20I%20was%20getting%20sick%20of%20gaming%2C%20and%20pivoted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrooming-and-style-hacks-for-guys-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emen's%20grooming%20and%20fashion%3C%2Fa%3E%20videos.%20Viewers%20were%20asking%20questions%20about%20what%20I%20was%20wearing%20and%20how%20I%20styled%20my%20hair.%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20training%20or%20even%20a%20passion%20for%20it%2C%20but%20the%20concept%20of%20self-improvement%20as%20a%20whole%20has%20always%20resonated%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20videos%20outperformed%20anything%20I%20had%20ever%20posted%2C%20and%20I%20started%20to%20gain%20traction%20with%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20set%20a%20goal.%20I%20told%20myself%20that%20once%20I'd%20saved%20%24100%2C000%2C%20I%20could%20quit.%20I%20achieved%20that%20by%20the%20end%20of%202017%2C%20and%20in%20early%202018%2C%20after%20almost%20three%20years%20at%20the%20company%2C%20I%20walked%20into%20my%20director's%20office%20and%20told%20him%20I%20was%20taking%20a%20leap%20of%20faith.%20He%20said%20he%20knew%20it%20was%20coming%2C%20but%20didn't%20realize%20it%20would%20be%20so%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-quit-after-two-decades-based-on-four-questions-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQuitting%3C%2Fa%3E%20YouTube%20was%20the%20toughest%2C%20scariest%2C%20and%20best%20career%20decision%20I've%20made%20in%20my%20life.%20I%20was%20scared%2C%20but%20there%20was%20no%20plan%20B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dbfdb2d6-4574-4cc2-94e1-26fa78be08fd%5C%22%3EI%20landed%20one%20of%20my%20first%206-figure%20brand%20deals%20a%20year%20after%20I%20left%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20became%20a%20millionaire%20as%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Finfluencers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einfluencer%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20starting%20my%20own%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20weren't%20many%20men's%20lifestyle%20influencers%20when%20I%20started%20%E2%80%94%20now%20it's%20almost%20the%20norm.%20But%20I%20was%20the%20top%20dog%20at%20the%20time%20and%20it%20was%20very%20profitable.%20In%202018%2C%20the%20year%20after%20I%20quit%2C%20I%20made%20five%20or%20six%20times%20my%20YouTube%20salary.%20I%20landed%20one%20of%20my%20first%20six-figure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-ways-influencers-find-brand-deals-key-takeaways-new-survey-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrand%20deals%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Old%20Spice%20roughly%20a%20year%20after%20I%20left%20YouTube.%20There%20were%20others%2C%20including%20with%20Whoop%20and%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHair%20has%20always%20been%20my%20No.%201%20topic%2C%20and%20reviewing%20products%20that%20sometimes%20had%20more%20feminine%20packaging%20or%20scents%20gave%20me%20the%20idea%20to%20develop%20my%20own%20brand.%20There%20was%20space%20for%20something%20that%20speaks%20directly%20to%20men%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20my%20audience%2C%20which%20is%20mostly%20male%2C%20could%20serve%20as%20the%20best%20feedback%20loop%20in%20developing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForte%20Series%20was%20completely%20bootstrapped%2C%20and%20I've%20never%20taken%20any%20money%20out%20of%20the%20company.%20We%20sold%20out%20of%20our%20first%20launch%20in%20October%202019%20%E2%80%94%20about%20%2450%2C000%20worth%20of%20product%20in%20a%20month%20and%20a%20half.%20Today%2C%20it%20has%20eight%20full-time%20employees%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20myself%20and%20my%20cofounder%2C%20Brian%20Yang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20we're%20growing.%20The%20company%20drove%20%243.8%20million%20in%20sales%20in%20one%20year%20starting%20April%201%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US.%20That's%20not%20counting%20other%20sales%20channels%20like%20Shopify%2C%20Amazon%20International%2C%20and%20the%20roughly%20100%20barbershops%20where%20it's%20available%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brand%20is%20on%20track%20to%20do%20%2410%20million%20in%20revenue%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e7d232e2-92fc-451d-8c9a-88cb106bc2fe%5C%22%3EA%20costly%20mistake%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20stumbles%20along%20the%20way.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20was%20trying%20to%20launch%20separate%20brands%20for%20skincare%20and%20clothing%2C%20Apricus%20and%20Aetos.%20The%20skincare%20has%20now%20been%20folded%20under%20Forte%2C%20and%20the%20clothing%20line%20has%20stopped%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20costly%20mistake%20because%20the%20same%20team%20was%20working%20on%20multiple%20brands%2C%20which%20created%20resource%20constraints%20because%20everyone's%20focus%20was%20split.%20We%20were%20also%20taking%20money%20from%20Forte%20to%20pay%20for%20purchase%20orders%20from%20the%20other%20brands%2C%20rather%20than%20reinvesting%20that%20money%20back%20into%20Forte%2C%20which%20was%20the%20real%20winner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20initially%20embarrassed%20about%20having%20to%20tell%20my%20audience%20that%20I'd%20failed%20as%20a%20businessman%2C%20including%20everyone%20who%20had%20supported%20me%20by%20buying%20the%20products.%20Thankfully%2C%20they%20were%20understanding%2C%20and%20as%20much%20as%20it%20hurt%2C%20it%20was%20also%20a%20huge%20weight%20off%20my%20shoulders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20look%20to%20the%20future%2C%20the%20scariest%20thing%20for%20a%20content%20creator%20is%20to%20be%20irrelevant.%20I%20get%20bored%20easily%2C%20and%20I've%20become%20good%20at%20being%20a%20chameleon.%20And%20I%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20to%20offer%20than%20just%20being%20the%20fashion%20and%20hair%20guy%20on%20YouTube.%20Recently%2C%20I%20started%20a%20new%20YouTube%20channel%20sharing%20more%20about%20my%20journey%20as%20an%20entrepreneur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20I%20just%20want%20to%20give%20guys%20confidence.%2