hey%20did%20have%20broke%2C%20they%20fixed%20it.%20Then%20the%20postwar%20economic%20boom%20and%20the%20%26quot%3BMad%20Men%26quot%3B%20era%20of%20advertising%2C%20and%20voil%C3%A0%2C%20stuff-palooza.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-americans-cant-stop-buying-shopping-addiction-stuff-consumer-spending-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnlimited%20amounts%20of%20things%20now%20surround%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3Eus%2C%20%3C%2Fu%3Eallowing%20us%20to%20take%20an%20on-to-the-next-one%20approach%20to%20consumption.%20When%20our%20phones%2C%20washing%20machines%2C%20or%20jeans%20show%20even%20a%20remote%20sign%20of%20wear%2C%20the%20path%20of%20least%20resistance%20is%20to%20replace%20them.%20Now%2C%20with%20President%20Donald%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-increase-prices-empty-shelves-timeline-supply-chain-holidays-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20threatening%20to%20increase%20prices%20and%20continuing%20concerns%20about%20inflation%2C%20that%20calculation%20may%20not%20be%20so%20straightforward.%20Repair%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20appealing.%20The%20problem%20is%2C%20it's%20a%20habit%20we've%20moved%20away%20from%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20that%20may%20be%20tough%20to%20get%20back%20to%20because%20of%20technological%2C%20financial%2C%20and%20cultural%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20throwaway%20replacement%20mentality%20has%20definitely%20increased%20dramatically%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nathan%20Proctor%2C%20who%20heads%20a%20right-to-repair%20campaign%20for%20the%20US%20Public%20Interest%20Research%20Group%2C%20an%20advocacy%20group.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20just%20churning%20through%20stuff%20at%20a%20ridiculous%20pace.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Americans%20want%20to%20avoid%20tariff-driven%20price%20jumps%2C%20they%20may%20want%20to%20put%20down%20their%20credit%20cards%20and%20pick%20up%20some%20duct%20tape%20or%20a%20screwdriver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20long%20and%20short%20of%20why%20we%20don't%20fix%20things%20anymore%20is%20that%20it's%20easy%20not%20to.%20New%20is%20often%20cheaper%2C%20faster%2C%20and%20more%20exciting%20than%20repairing%20the%20old.%20That's%20by%20design%2C%20in%20large%20part%2C%20from%20corporate%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20companies%20have%20business%20models%20that%20rely%20on%20the%20frequent%20replacement%20of%20their%20products%2C%20said%20Aaron%20Perzanowski%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan.%20He%20pointed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20a%20history%20of%20making%20its%20devices%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-supports-bill-making-it-easier-to-repair-iphone-mac-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etough%20for%20consumers%20to%20repair%3C%2Fa%3E%20(though%20that's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-ios-18-update-repair-assistant-repair-iphone-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarting%20to%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20margins).%20%26quot%3BThe%20number%20of%20phones%20that%20they%20have%20to%20sell%20every%20year%20to%20keep%20shareholders%20happy%20is%20jaw-dropping%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20better%20for%20Apple%20if%20you%20buy%20a%20brand-new%20%24900%20iPhone%20than%20spend%20%2490%20on%20a%20new%20battery%20or%20give%20%2425%20to%20some%20small%20local%20shop%20to%20replace%20your%20cracked%20screen.%20The%20company%20spends%20a%20lot%20of%20energy%20on%20getting%20you%20to%20do%20that%2C%20via%20design%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20other%20strategies.%20%26quot%3BThey%20refuse%20to%20sell%20replacement%20parts%20to%20consumers%2C%20or%20they%20use%20software%20locks%20that%20frustrate%20repairs.%20Even%20if%20you're%20using%20authorized%20original%20manufacturer%20components%2C%20they%20leverage%20intellectual%20property%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20They%20also%20employ%20%26quot%3Brelentless%20messaging%20about%20the%20value%20of%20newness%26quot%3B%20to%20make%20consumers%20feel%20like%20they%20must%20have%20the%20hot%20new%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20how%20good%20businesses%20have%20gotten%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheap-stuff-economy-prices-american-dream-housing-televisions-tariffs-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproducing%20inexpensive%20stuff%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20televisions%20to%20toys%2C%20it's%20often%20cheaper%20for%20them%20to%20make%20a%20new%20thing%20than%20to%20invest%20in%20a%20network%20of%20professional%20repair%20technicians.%20Engineering%20is%20focused%20on%20cheap%20production%2C%20and%20repairability%20isn't%20a%20consideration.%20Building%20something%20in%20the%20least%20expensive%20way%20possible%20is%20not%20conducive%20to%20building%20it%20to%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRepair%20requires%20a%20human%20being%20with%20arms%20and%20hands%20and%20fingers%20and%20skill%20and%20expertise%2C%20and%20building%20a%20new%20one%20often%20requires%20a%20factory%20full%20of%20robots%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20Perzanowski%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20the%20scale%20just%20does%20not%20work%20for%20making%20repair%20an%20economical%20proposition%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20instances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20businesses%20have%20been%20accused%20of%20deliberately%20making%20their%20products%20hard%20to%20fix%20by%20third%20parties%20%E2%80%94%20they%20make%20manuals%20and%20parts%20difficult%2C%20if%20not%20impossible%2C%20to%20find.%20They%20might%20require%20expensive%20software%20plug-ins%20or%20program%20products%20to%20lock%20up%20if%20the%20wrong%20party%20tries%20to%20tinker%20with%20them.%20In%20January%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2025%2F01%2Fftc-states-sue-deere-company-protect-farmers-unfair-corporate-tactics-high-repair-costs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esued%3C%2Fa%3E%20John%20Deere%20over%20the%20draconian%20repair%20setup%20for%20its%20farm%20equipment%2C%20such%20as%20tractors%20and%20combines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BManufacturers%20have%20thrown%20up%20barriers%20that%20made%20it%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kyle%20Wiens%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20iFixit%2C%20an%20online%20platform%20that%20provides%20repair%20guides%2C%20tools%2C%20and%20parts%20for%20thousands%20of%20products.%20They%20also%20publish%20repairability%20scores%2C%20so%20consumers%20know%20how%20likely%20they'll%20be%20able%20to%20fix%20what%20they're%20buying%20ahead%20of%20time.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20always%20trying%20to%20say%2C%20how%20do%20we%20make%20it%20as%20easy%20as%20possible%2C%20easier%2C%20to%20maintain%20the%20things%20that%20we've%20got%20rather%20than%20to%20replace%20it%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShelie%20Miller%2C%20a%20sustainable%20systems%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20supply%20chains%20have%20also%20become%20so%20complicated%20that%20even%20collecting%20the%20parts%20to%20fix%20something%20is%20a%20herculean%20task.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20to%20take%20apart%20an%20air%20fryer%20right%20now%2C%20it%20is%20virtually%20impossible%20to%20quickly%20get%20at%20all%20of%20the%20components%20if%20something%20went%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20you'd%20have%20to%20spend%20hours%20potentially%20disassembling%20the%20interface%20of%20a%20very%20small%20household%20appliance%20just%20to%20get%20the%20circuitry%20not%20built%20or%20designed%20for%20anyone%20to%20take%20it%20apart%20later.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20tempting%20to%20place%20the%20blame%20for%20why%20we%20don't%20fix%20things%20anymore%20entirely%20on%20corporations%2C%20there's%20a%20pervasive%20cultural%20factor%20involved%20as%20well%3A%20American%20consumers%20love%20to%20cycle%20through%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20live%20in%20a%20throwaway%20society%20that%20largely%20prefers%20to%20ignore%20the%20consequences%20of%20our%20constant%20consumerism%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20environment%2C%20to%20our%20communities%2C%20to%20workers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-micro-trends-cause-financial-problems-fashion-mental-health-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrotrends%3C%2Fa%3E%20make%20us%20feel%20like%20new%20is%20always%20better%2C%20so%20we%20don't%20even%20consider%20patching%20last%20year's%20jeans.%20Many%20Americans%20judge%20each%20other%20over%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-doj-lawsuit-antitrust-green-bubble-samsung-stigma-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephones%20they%20have%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20whether%20that%20device%20is%20the%20latest%20version.%20Buying%20a%20fresh%20thing%20gives%20us%20a%20little%20dopamine%20hit%20that%20doesn't%20happen%20when%20we%20revive%20something%20we%20already%20have.%20Even%20though%20that%20dopamine%20hit%20is%20short-lived%2C%20it's%20alluring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20been%20warped%20by%20amazing%20marketing%20organizations%20that%20tell%20us%20that%20every%20single%20year%20the%20latest%20and%20greatest%20thing%20has%20come%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lauren%20Benton%2C%20the%20general%20manager%20of%20Back%20Market%2C%20an%20e-commerce%20platform%20that%20sells%20refurbished%20devices%20from%20phones%20to%20beard%20trimmers.%20Part%20of%20her%20company's%20mission%20is%20to%20get%20people%20to%20think%20about%20whether%20the%20latest%20version%20of%20whatever%20device%20is%20noticeably%20different%20from%20previous%20versions%20and%20open%20their%20minds%20to%20something%20that's%20been%20fixed%20up.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20these%20stigmas%20around%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20are%20here%20to%20tell%20them%20about%20the%20financial%20savings%2C%20the%20environmental%20savings%20of%20choosing%20refurbished.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20eschew%20the%20new%2C%20we've%20lost%20much%20of%20the%20cultural%20know-how%20around%20repair.%20Many%20of%20the%20local%20shops%20that%20repaired%20appliances%2C%20televisions%2C%20and%20radios%20have%20closed%20down%2C%20and%20those%20types%20of%20jobs%20have%20gone%20away.%20The%20types%20of%20skills%20needed%20in%20those%20jobs%20have%20changed%2C%20too%2C%20as%20technology%20has%20evolved.%20Plus%2C%20companies%20have%20made%20it%20harder%20for%20them%20to%20exist%2C%20instead%20funneling%20customers%20to%20their%20preferred%20stores%20or%20in-house%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20wanted%20to%20fix%20did%20it%20as%20independents%2C%26quot%3B%20Proctor%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20the%20manufacturers%20realized%20that%20the%20more%20independents%20there%20were%2C%20the%20worse%20it%20was%20for%20their%20authorized%20programs%2C%20the%20more%20it%20was%20competing%20with%20their%20new%20sales.%20And%20so%20they%20erected%20a%20whole%20set%20of%20legal%20and%20business%20practices%20that%20attempted%20to%20make%20it%20impossible%20for%20those%20repair%20shops%20to%20operate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guy%20down%20the%20street%20who%20can%20fix%20your%20computer%20probably%20no%20longer%20exists%20in%20your%20local%20community%2C%20though%20he%20does%20exist%20online.%20People%20can%20mail%20in%20their%20devices%2C%20or%20they%20can%20find%20communities%20and%20videos%20with%20information%20to%20help%20them%20fix%20things%20themselves.%20It's%20good%20that%20the%20internet%20has%20endless%20resources%2C%20but%20it%20still%20puts%20the%20onus%20on%20individual%20consumers%2C%20and%20the%20repair%20still%20isn't%20as%20convenient%20as%20the%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENirav%20Patel%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Framework%2C%20which%20makes%20repairable%20electronics%20such%20as%20laptops%2C%20told%20me%20many%20of%20his%20earliest%20customers%20were%20tech%20enthusiasts%20and%20DIYers.%20The%20company%20has%20also%20started%20to%20garner%20interest%20from%20people%20concerned%20about%20the%20environment.%20In%20Patel's%20experience%2C%20teaching%20people%20to%20alter%20and%20fix%20Framework%20devices%20hasn't%20necessarily%20been%20a%20skills%20question%20but%20a%20confidence%20one.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20of%20the%20mental%20barrier%20of%20seeing%20something%20like%20a%20computer%20as%20an%20object%20that%20can%20be%20opened%2C%20that%20has%20parts%20inside%20that%20you%20can%20swap%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGay%20Gordon-Byrne%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20The%20Repair%20Association%2C%20which%20backs%20the%20right-to-repair%20movement%2C%20said%20we%20need%20to%20%26quot%3Bdemystify%26quot%3B%20repair.%20Just%20as%20schools%20used%20to%20teach%20students%20to%20type%20or%20put%20them%20in%20home%20economics%20and%20shop%20classes%2C%20electronics%20repair%20classes%20should%20be%20added%20to%20the%20curriculum.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20modern%20version%20of%20needle%20and%20thread%2C%20the%20modern%20version%20of%20putting%20air%20in%20your%20tires%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20how%20our%20stuff%20works%2C%20or%20at%20least%20having%20a%20fair%20number%20of%20people%20who%20understand%20it%2C%20isn't%20just%20beneficial%20on%20an%20individual%20consumer%20level%3B%20it%20also%20helps%20collectively%20safeguard%20us%20from%20getting%20ripped%20off%20or%20being%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20there's%20a%20severe%20knowledge%20imbalance%20with%20manufacturers.%20We%20are%20better%20positioned%20to%20critique%20and%20regulate%20technology%20when%20we%20understand%20how%20it%20works%20and%20its%20machinations.%20One%20way%20to%20learn%20how%20stuff%20works%20is%20to%20be%20able%20to%20disassemble%20it%20and%20reverse%20engineer%20it.%20It's%20a%20valuable%20skill%20that%20America%2C%20collectively%2C%20should%20not%20want%20to%20lose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20also%20become%20particularly%20useful%20in%20the%20short%20term%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftrump-tariffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20take%20hold.%20Many%20items%20are%20expected%20to%20get%20more%20expensive%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-increases-trump-tariffs-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eif%20their%20prices%20haven't%20gone%20up%20already%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20some%20goods%20may%20be%20harder%20to%20get%20overall.%20People%20have%20already%20been%20leaning%20toward%20keeping%20their%20things%20for%20longer%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-prices-inflation-soaring-corporate-greed-profits-margins-wages-jobs-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20post-pandemic%20bout%20of%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20this%20may%20push%20them%20even%20further.%20The%20buy%20new%20versus%20fix%20old%20calculation%20is%20evolving%20as%20prices%20continue%20to%20creep%20up%2C%20compelling%20more%20of%20us%20to%20become%20tinkerers%2C%20even%20if%20reluctantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20solution%20for%20how%20to%20revive%20the%20practice%20of%20repair%20is%20complicated.%20We're%20not%20going%20to%20all%20wake%20up%20tomorrow%20and%20decide%20to%20break%20open%20the%20dishwasher%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20that%20noise%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20policy%20level%2C%20the%20right-to-repair%20movement%20is%20making%20headway%20in%20compelling%20companies%20to%20allow%20consumers%20to%20fix%20their%20own%20products%20or%20contract%20with%20independent%20professionals%20to%20do%20so%20instead%20of%20going%20to%20the%20manufacturer.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20create%20competition%20and%20make%20fixing%20things%20less%20expensive%20and%20less%20onerous.%20Right-to-repair%20legislation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpirg.org%2Fmedia-center%2Frelease-all-50-states-now-have-filed-right-to-repair-legislation-over-last-8-years%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20passed%20in%20seven%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20bills%20have%20been%20filed%20in%20all%2050%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20saying%2C%20'Wait%20a%20second%2C%20what%20do%20you%20mean%20I%20can't%20fix%20my%20stuff%3F'%20And%20then%20they%20read%20about%20right%20to%20repair%20and%20they%20say%2C%20'Hell%2C%20yeah%2C'%26quot%3B%20Gordon-Byrne%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20more%20grassroots%20level%2C%20fix-it%20clinics%20and%20repair%20caf%C3%A9s%2C%20where%20people%20gather%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20fix%20their%20stuff%20or%20meet%20someone%20who%20can%2C%20have%20begun%20to%20pop%20up.%20There%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20always%20the%20internet%20and%20the%20bottomless%20sea%20of%20how-to%20videos%20on%20YouTube.%20Some%20organizations%20are%20focusing%20on%20education%2C%20too.%20In%20New%20York%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Materials%20for%20the%20Arts%2C%20a%20reuse%20center%20that%20gathers%20and%20distributes%20creative%20materials%20to%20local%20schools%20and%20organizations%2C%20launched%20a%20repair%20program%20in%202023%20that%20teaches%20students%20how%20to%20fix%20items%20in%20its%20warehouse.%20They%20learn%20to%20reupholster%20furniture%2C%20sew%20costumes%2C%20and%20fix%20bikes%2C%20which%20can%20open%20pathways%20to%20a%20possible%20trade%20or%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20way%20for%20us%20to%20engage%20with%20students%20that%20are%20maybe%20on%20the%20fence%20about%20what%20their%20future%20is%20going%20to%20be%20and%20what%20they're%20interested%20in%2C%20and%20give%20them%20a%20hands-on%20lesson%20on%20just%20being%20resourceful%20and%20using%20their%20hands%20and%20learning%20about%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Tara%20Sansone%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20Materials%20for%20the%20Arts%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20consumerist%20culture%20is%20perhaps%20the%20most%20difficult%20piece%20of%20this%20resistance%20to%20repair%20to%20unpack.%20It%20is%20easy%20and%20tempting%20to%20just%20toss%20our%20things%20and%20get%20something%20else.%20People%20are%20busy%2C%20and%20new%20things%20are%20generally%20cheap.%20It's%20annoying%20that%20many%20of%20our%20goods%20aren't%20as%20durable%20as%20they%20used%20to%20be.%20It's%20even%20more%20annoying%20to%20spend%20twice%20the%20amount%20on%20a%20repair%20than%20a%20new%20item%20would%20cost%20or%20lose%20endless%20hours%20down%20a%20YouTube%20rabbit%20hole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20posed%20this%20cultural%20conundrum%20to%20experts%2C%20I%20got%20two%20buckets%20of%20responses%20%E2%80%94%20they%20either%20told%20me%20that%20fixing%20things%20wasn't%20that%20hard%2C%20or%20they%20said%20it's%20the%20type%20of%20problem%20that's%20hard%20to%20solve.%20One%20person%20explained%20that%20I%20actually%20can%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20fix%20my%20TV%20if%20I%20give%20it%20a%20bit%20of%20effort%2C%20a%20point%20on%20which%20I%20beg%20to%20differ.%20Another%20said%20they%20occasionally%20pretend%20to%20be%20the%20fix-it%20type%20but%20acknowledged%20that's%20not%20the%20norm%2C%20which%20I%20will%20take%20as%20absolution%20for%20my%20future%20sin%20of%20tossing%20my%20TV.%20I%20figure%20I%20can%20alleviate%20some%20guilt%20by%20recycling%20it%2C%20though%20Anna%20Sacks%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20waste%20expert%20who%20goes%20by%20The%20Trash%20Walker%20online%2C%20told%20me%20that's%20not%20really%20ideal%2C%20either.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20better%20to%20repair%20a%20microwave%20than%20recycle%20a%20microwave%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20(Luckily%20for%20my%20guilt%20index%2C%20I%20do%20not%20own%20a%20microwave.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%2C%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20said%20initiatives%20such%20as%20right-to-repair%20legislation%20help%2C%20but%20the%20cultural%20shift%20is%20the%20much%20thornier%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what%20needs%20to%20happen%20in%20order%20to%20reshift%20our%20mindset%20to%20actually%20valuing%20stuff%20and%20saying%2C%20'Oh%2C%20wow%2C%20this%20actually%20is%20a%20valuable%20material%20and%20we%20shouldn't%20just%20be%20throwing%20it%20away%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20it%2C%20I%20think%2C%20does%20come%20down%20to%20the%20economics%20of%20if%20our%20goods%20are%20incredibly%20cheap%2C%20it's%20much%20easier%20to%20have%20this%20consumption%20and%20throwaway%20lifestyle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tariffs-americans-learn-to-fix-things-repair-prices-savings-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746087422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68127ce7a466d2b74ab4a3fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tariffs-americans-learn-to-fix-things-repair-prices-savings-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20Americans%20want%20to%20avoid%20higher%20prices%20from%20Trump's%20tariffs%2C%20they%20may%20want%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20repair%20the%20stuff%20they%20already%20own.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A58%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tariffs-americans-learn-to-fix-things-repair-prices-savings-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Don't%20demoral